items.abstract: A remarkably selective system for transfer hydrogenation of alkenes, composed of Grubbs’ ruthenium metathesis catalyst and HCOONa/HCOOH, is presented. This system can also be formed directly after a metathesis reaction to effect hydrogenation in a single-pot.
title: In tandem or alone: a remarkably selective transfer hydrogenation of alkenes catalyzed by ruthenium olefin metathesis catalysts

items.abstract: <jats:p>The article presents the results of numerical and experimental investigations concerning contact coordinate measurements of complex ceramic parts made of Al<jats:sub>2</jats:sub>O<jats:sub>3</jats:sub> and ZrO<jats:sub>2</jats:sub> based ceramic materials in different states. The investigated parts were manufactured by using two machining processes: ultrasonic assisted grinding and conventional grinding. The results of investigations may be used in order to improve the manufacturing process of geometrically complex ceramic parts.</jats:p>
title: Coordinate Measurements of Geometrically Complex Ceramic Parts
